content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were travelling by car from sydney to canberra on 31-12-92, intending to spend new years eve with relatives in canberra. it was a clear sunny day. at approximately 1-30 pm we were approximately forty five kilometres from canberra, and close to a vineyard called lake george winery. i negotiated a bend in the road, and immediately saw an object in the sky some distance ahead, at a low altitude. my first thoughts were that i was observing a head on view of a boeing 747. this aroused some consternation, as i knew that canberra airport did not have a runway capable of handling a 747, and i could not understand why a 747 would be at such a low altitude. the road lapsed into several bends with some trees, and i lost sight of the object. after negotiating the bends, the road was then straight for a couple of kilometres. as soon as i came through the bends, we both regained our view of the object, only then, it was a full side view, and we both were astonished to see a rocket shaped craft, hovering at approximately 100 metres above some low hills to the north, with these hills in turn, approximately 190 metres above the road we were on. i have calculated these measurements using google earth. i stopped the car, and we got out and further observed the object. we were approximately 800 metres from the object. the object was a classical rocket shape, approximately 45 metres in length, approximately 6 metres in diameter, slightly tapering towards the rear. it was a grey colour, and there was a single row of windows for nearly the full length. i do not recall the exact shape of the windows, only that they were there. there were no protrusions whatsoever on the outside of this object. there was a cloud of steam like vapour around the tail end of this object, no sign of pressure, more like steam from a parked steam locomotive. i had a cam recorder in the car and retrieved it, and attempted to take a movie of the object, and my camera would not switch on. yet i used it later in canberra without a problem. suddenly the object just disappeared, one minute it was there, and then it disappeared. the cloud of steam like vapour stayed in the sky for a few more seconds before disappearing.
content.summary: Rocket shaped object seen

content.detailedDescription: I was working 3 miles south of town i stopped working for a moment walked to my pickup to grab a water while walking i looked at the sky because there was a large contrail from a jet,while looking at that i noticed a shiny object flying just above the contrail at first i believed it was another jet at a higher altitude it wasn't moving at a speed that would suggest otherwise.After watching the object for a few minutes i noticed it was a sphere and it was much brighter than a plane reflecting sunlight the object stopped flying east to west hovered just above the contrail for approximately 5 minutes then suddenly went straight vertical for what i can only assume to be 2 -3 thousand feet after reaching that altitude the object hovered for around 10 more minutes and then seemed to vanish i did take a few photos hoping to capture a image which i did but it is a cell phone photo so quality isn't the greatest i did contact a friend during the event to see if he could see the object from where he was and he could not after that i checked my photos and to my relief i captured 1 decent picture

content.detailedDescription: I was driving on i-394 heading north (from dyer, in) heading back to chicago. out of the corner of my eye, i noticed some lights in the sky to my right (east).  traffic was light, so i slowed down a bit to get a better look (i noticed the other cars also hit their brakes to slow down).  i saw 4-5 large, hazy white lights chasing each other in a perfect circle, going through whatever clouds were there, and then meeting up in the middle of the circle and then going back into the circle formation.  looked like they were playing ring around the rosie, but at a fast pace.  i looked at the time and it was 7:55 pm.  i kept sight of it until i got onto i-294 and then couldn't look up because traffic was pretty busy on i-294. got off on my exit to head home. i was at a light on 107th pulaski in chicago heading north and looked up and a bit to my left (west), and there they were - the lights chasing each other in a perfect circle in and out of the clouds and meeting in the middle, bouncing back out to the circle - once again. i believe it was about 8:20 pm. during both sightings, i did not see any beams of light beneath it going to the ground as one might see with a spotlight or advertising lights; no storms or lightning in area. i know other people saw this as well, as i saw people looking from their cars in that direction. perhaps they may report it as well. it wasn't the first time i've witnessed this phenomenon.  i saw this at least two other times, once with my son. sure would like to know if anyone else witnessed this!
content.summary: 4-5 white hazy lights chasing each other in a circle, no spotlight or beacon underneath

content.detailedDescription: I am an ex-militery pilot and know what an aircraft at high altitude on a clear night looks like. i also know what flares look like when viewed from a distance. what i saw when going out on the driveway of my house at approx. 8:00pm central time (dark and cloudless sky with full moon) looked like two very bright stars next to each other and stationary in the sky. these starlike objects were a good bit brighter than venus. i obviously have never seen 2 stars that were this bright and postioned right next to each other. these objects were not blinking or changing color from there white star-like appearance. i vewed them for about one minute. after 1 full minute, both stars started to dim slowly untill i could not see them anymore. from the time they were at full brightness untill they could not be seen anymore took about 30 seconds. while they were dimming, they remained in there same position in the sky ... i have never in my life seen anything like this before. these 2 objects looked to be in outerspace (such as you would see a star or venus) ... in my opinion, they were not at an lower altitude where any aircraft would be. i feel so lucky that for the first time in my life (i am now 69 years old), that i have seen something that i am convinced is not anything from that can be explained as natural or manmade. i did not have a camera or a cell phone on my person, so unfortunatly i have no photos or video .... ron larson
content.summary: 2 bright star-like object brighter that venus and stationary next to each other. then both dimmed and disapeared

content.detailedDescription:
I live on a 9 acre ranch in rural riverside county, california.  the ranch sits in a canyon approximately 1.5-2 miles across.  from my property, i only have light noise that comes from the nw from the town of redlands 10 miles away.

the object i spotted was due east with little to no visible light noise from the canyon.

what caught my eye was the object was twinkling extremely bright randomly  changing colors through most of the color spectrum. it also seemed to be much closer than other stars.

at that point i grabbed my camera (nikon d5200 w/nikkor 55-300mm lens mounted on tripod) and set it up in my driveway pointed due east approximately 10 degrees above the horizon and video recorded about 5 minutes worth of footage until my battery died.  during the recording, the object seemed to move with earths orbit, but about half way through the video i noticed it made a slight direction change to the south just prior to moving out of the field of view of my camera (i did not adjust the tripod once i started recording).

with limited time, i wasn't able to view the video for a few days.  once i did see the video, i was amazed with what i captured.  this object seemed to be within the earths atmosphere after view a freeze frame.  what also made me believe this was within the atmosphere is that no other stars  were picked up with my camera which was set to record the flashing orb i spotted.
content.summary: Spotted flashing orb due east of san timoteo canyon in riverside county california

content.detailedDescription:
I was watching television at 10 pm.  suddenly i felt an intense urge to go to the end of the hall and open the back window, something i don't usually do.  i leaned out, looked up and saw some stars through the branches of our huge eucalyptus tree.  one reddish white star was brighter than the others.  i looked for the pulsing red light of an airplane, but its light was solid. 
i watched it for about 10-15 seconds before i realized the reddish white star was moving.  then the ufo jumped from the top middle of the branches to the top right (as viewed through the branches).  it moved erratically to the right of the tree and into clear sky where it began moving in a square shape for a few seconds.  then it simply vanished.  i ran out onto our deck to see if the ufo was visible somewhere else in the sky but it was gone.  
i feel like this ufo was trying to communicate with me. it's an uneasy feeling.  i just keep thinking how did i know to get up and walk to the end of the hall and open the window to see this thing?  i almost feel as if i had been summoned to see it.   also, this is the second ufo i've seen in the past year.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: I saw a moving starlike reddish white ufo at night

content.detailedDescription:
1. we were sitting out on our deck at 9:23pm
2. looking up we noticed four little circular lights in the sky. 
3. we thought they were lights that were made from projections, similar to batman's bat signal, but we saw no beam leading up to them. 
4. the lights hovered around the area, never going far. they seemed to be moving around within a certain area, as if dancing in a way. we could see the lights in the clouds, but they'd become obscure for a few minutes before reappearing and continue to move in an non-patterned way. 
5. this was a very hands off, observation only encounter, if it is at all. we were excited and intrigued but not frightened or worried in any way. 
6. they eventually vanished similar to how they did with the clouds but never emerged again. 

all pictures were taken with an iphone 7, i attempted to video record but it was too dark to capture the lights pointing it at the sky. so i resorted to photos. we aren't sure these are extraterrestrial, but we're curious to see what you all think.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Other
content.summary: Sitting on our deck, see 4 lights in the sky, moving around/hovering, for 83 minutes

[the next night after this i saw another one in the same area at 8 pm, actually two of them which appeared out of nowhere and flew the same way as the first night.]

content.detailedDescription:
While at the end of my drive way i noticed what looked like a tight cluster of flashing red lights hovering toward the north of my location.  i estimate the lights were no more then 1/4 mile away at an altitude of 500 to 1000'.  the cluster of lights appeared to be part of one aircraft.  i did not notice any white or green lights which are normally associated with helicopters or airplanes.  
the strangest part of my observation was when the lights quickly moved from left to right in a straight line.  the lights kept moving left to right, hover for a second, and then move back right to left and hover.  it did this very quickly and would come to a hover each time.  the lights were not moving in racetrack pattern which is a very common pattern for a helicopter but a straight line. i kept saying to myself "how can these lights do this".  it just didn't look normal for a helicopter to do this kind of flight. 
here's where it gets really weird.  after the lights had gone back and forth in this straight pattern a couple of times they disappeared only to reappear a short distance away.  the lights would appear to hover and then disappear.  one second later they would reappear a short distance away.  the lights did this three times before rapidly descending below the horizon.  i believe the object was leaving the area by moving away from my location as the lights became smaller and faded in brightness. 
weather:
it was a clear night with no ceiling.  there were numerous fixed wing aircraft in the area.  i live just 8 miles from north east philadelphia airport (pne). 
flight radar 24:
i used a program called "flightradar24" to look around the time frame that i saw the lights.  it didn't show any helicopters in the area of interest.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Flashing object flying erratic low in the sky

content.detailedDescription:
Report submitted by ryan stacey, ci and pd for ontario. speaking to witness over the phone.

witness has had multiple occurrences where time had been lost and unaccounted for. the latest event involved an orb located at the location provided above. 

on another night the witness observed strange looking lightening and as he looked up to a clear sky he observed a round object appear and travel south to north. the object is described as a bright white and being smaller then a penny. 

one night the witness woke up with blood at the end of the bed by where the witnesses feet were. his wife had pointed out the blood and inquired, the witness was sleeping prior and has no recollection. there were no wounds or lesions on the witnesses feet. the witness then spoke to family doctor who had no explanation for the occurrence at the time, - the mysterious blood was since washed away.  

the witness claims to not have any sleep paralysis or deprivation diagnosis. there is no history of sleep walking nor does the witness take any medications that would directly effect any sleeping habits.

on another night, both the witness and his wife had gone to sleep in there bed together as per usual. when they awoke, the witness noticed that the mattress above the box spring had shifted 4 inches to the right side in favor of where the witness sleeps. upon discovering this, neither the wife or the witness recall any tremors or movement during the course of the night that would have caused the bed to shift.
content.summary: More the one occurrence has happened that involved missing time

4. observed two bright white blue flashes in the sky to the west. similar to a match being ignited the first became lit with the second becoming bright two seconds later. seemed to be 100 times brighter than the brightest star in the sky. the flare-up lasted less than 3 seconds. the brightness of both were reduced to that of a typical satellite. the second object followed the first for about 20 seconds. the first object changed course at approximately a 45 degree angle. the second object also changed course at a 45 degree angle when it reached the spot where the first one altered course. this continued for over 10 minutes the first object changing course with the second mirroring with perfect redundancy. i observed changing of course eight to ten times over the 10 minutes. lost sight of the objects out of view to the east.
